wekatweeter.tools
Class WeightHandler

java.lang.Object
  wekatweeter.tools.WeightHandler

public class WeightHandler
extends java.lang.Object

Weight handler for the ARFF file. Calculates the weights for the tweet data using positive and negative terms present in a data instance.

Provides additional functionalities such as normalizing the data weights.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Muhammad Sajawal Javaid

calcNeutralDeviation

public double calcNeutralDeviation(java.lang.String input)
Calculates the initial weights of the neutral instances provided. The weight is essentially the deviation of the instance's polarity from a neutral baseline (neither positive nor negative).

Parameters:
input - A tweet data instance.
Returns:
The deviation of instance's polarity from the neutral baseline.

finalizeNeutralWeights

public DynamicArray<TweeterToken> finalizeNeutralWeights(DynamicArray<TweeterToken> data)
Finalizes the calculation for the weights for neutral category instances. Has to be performed separately as the instances must have an existing weight associated with them, which is the deviation from a neutral score. The higher this score (existing weight), the lower the resulting weight would be.

Parameters:
data - Weighted tweet data set.
Returns:
Tweet data set with final neutral instance weights.

normalizeWeights

Normalizes the weights of instances belonging to the specified category by finding the maximum weight and dividing all the weights by that weight.

Parameters:

category - Category to normalize the weights for.
